cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.IT 

This paper deals with the design of a MAC protocol for wireless networks using deep reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also extensively uses neural networks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of reinforcement learning algorithms also suggests that it could belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
